You are working on "Ops Graphic Generator", a React + TypeScript + Vite app that composes NATO military map symbols (APP-6 / MIL-STD-2525) from PNG assets onto an HTML Canvas.

Key architecture points:
- All state lives in App.tsx as a single SymbolState object (no state library)
- Rendering happens in src/utils/compositor.ts via drawComposite() which layers PNGs on a canvas
- Asset definitions are in src/data/ (symbols.ts, modifiers.ts, sizes.ts)
- Types are in src/types/index.ts
- Static PNGs are in "Ops Graphics/" (Vite publicDir) — do not modify these binary files
- There are no tests configured

When modifying modifier behavior:
- fillRatio (0-1) controls how much of the cell a modifier fills
- scaleMode ('fit'|'cover'|'stretch') controls aspect ratio handling
- shapePadding on base symbols (0-0.2) insets bounds for non-rectangular frames
- "Full-frame" icons (infantry, recon) use stretch mode per APP-6 standard
- Normal icons use fit mode with reduced fillRatio

Prefer minimal changes. This is a small focused app (~12 source files).
